âœ… SETUP Configuring user information used across all local repositories

âž¡ git config --global user.name
 â€œ[firstname lastname]â€ -> set a name that is identifiable for credit when reviewing version history
âž¡ git config --global user.email
 â€œ[valid-email]â€ -> set an email address that will be associated with each history marker
âž¡ git config --global colour.ui -> auto set automatic command line colouring for Git for easy reviewing
âž¡ git config --list -> Check global configuration details

âœ… SETUP & INIT

Configuring user information, initializing and cloning repositories

âž¡ git init ->initialize an existing directory as a Git repository
âž¡ git clone [url] ->retrieves an entire repository from a hosted location via UR

âœ… SHARE & UPDATE

Retrieving updates from another repository and updating local repos

âž¡ git remote add [alias] [URL] -> add a git URL as an alias
âž¡ git fetch [alias] -> fetch down all the branches from that Git remote
âž¡ git merge [alias]/[branch] -> merge a remote branch into your current branch to bring it up to date
âž¡ git push [alias] [branch] -> Transmit local branch commits to the remote repository branch
âž¡ git pull -> to fetch and merge any commits from the tracking remote branch

âœ… INSPECT & COMPARE

Examining logs, diffs and object information

âž¡ git log -> shows the commit history for the currently active branch
âž¡ git log branchB..branchA -> shows the commits on branchA that are not on branchB
âž¡ git log --follow [file] -> show the commits that changed the file, even across renames
âž¡ git diff branchB...branchA -> shows the diff of what is in branchA that is not in branchB
âž¡ git show [SHA] -> shows any object in Git in a human-readable format